      "title": "Conversion of degree to radian and vice versa",
      "conceptBody": "<h3><strong>Relation between Degree &amp; Radian&nbsp;</strong></h3><p>$\\pi $ radian $=180$ degree</p><p>$\\therefore \\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ }1$ radian $=\\frac{180}{\\pi }$ degree</p><p>or $\\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ }1$ degree $=\\frac{\\pi }{180}$ radian</p><p><strong>Trignometric Ratios of some Angles</strong></p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Angle</td><td>0</td><td>30</td><td>45</td><td>60</td><td>90</td><td>120</td><td>135</td><td>150</td><td>180</td></tr><tr><td>Sine</td><td>0</td><td>&nbsp; $\\frac{1}{2}$</td><td>$\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2}}$</td><td>$\\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2}$</td><td>1</td><td>$\\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2}$</td><td>$\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2}}$</td><td>$\\frac{1}{2}$</td><td>0</td></tr><tr><td>Cosine</td><td>1</td><td>&nbsp;$\\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2}$</td><td>$\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2}}$</td><td>$\\frac{1}{2}$</td><td>0</td><td>$-\\frac{1}{2}$</td><td>$-\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2}}$</td><td>$-\\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2}$</td><td>-1</td></tr><tr><td>Tangent</td><td>0</td><td>&nbsp;$\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}}$</td><td>&nbsp;1</td><td>$\\sqrt{3}$</td><td>$\\infty $</td><td>$-\\sqrt{3}$</td><td>-1</td><td>$-\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}}$</td><td>0</td></tr><tr><td>Cotangent</td><td>$\\infty $</td><td>&nbsp;$\\sqrt{3}$</td><td>&nbsp;1</td><td>$\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}}$</td><td>0</td><td>$-\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}}$</td><td>-1</td><td>$-\\sqrt{3}$</td><td>$\\infty $</td></tr><tr><td>Cosecant</td><td>$\\infty $</td><td>&nbsp; 2</td><td>$\\sqrt{2}$</td><td>$\\frac{2}{\\sqrt{3}}$</td><td>1</td><td>$\\frac{2}{\\sqrt{3}}$</td><td>$\\sqrt{2}$</td><td>2</td><td>$\\infty $</td></tr><tr><td>Secant</td><td>1</td><td>&nbsp;$\\frac{2}{\\sqrt{3}}$</td><td>$\\sqrt{2}$</td><td>2</td><td>$\\infty $</td><td>-2</td><td>$-\\sqrt{2}$</td><td>$-\\frac{2}{\\sqrt{3}}$</td><td>-1</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>",
